author: COMSOL
description:
An evanescent mode cavity filter can be realized by adding a structure inside of the cavity. This structure changes the resonant frequency below that of the dominant mode of the unfilled cavity. A piezo actuator is used to control the size of a small air gap which provides the tunability of the resonant frequency.

In addition to the RF Module, this example requires one of the Acoustics Module, the MEMS Module, or the Structural Mechanics Module.
